<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-498-581  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 498 581.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Magazine  Oct 30 1990 v9 n18 p44(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Phips: for color reduction. (Software Review) (TerraVisionProfessional High-Resolution Image Processing System graphicssoftware)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Simon, Barry.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   TerraVision Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Phips (Computer graphics software) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     EvaluationSoftware packagesGraphics Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Phips, short for Professional High-resolution Image Processing System, is a$349 DOS-based color-reduction program from TerraVision, the makers of thehighly respected bit-mapped file-conversion program TGL+.andP;  Throughsophisticated algorithms, Phips does a fine job of taking full-color imagesfrom formats such as Targa (16-, 24- or 32-bit formats) and rendering theimage with reduced color for desktop publishing or PC-based presentations.andM;Phips can reduce and then display Targa images on EGA and VGA screens andsupports a resolution of up to 800 by 600 by 256 on a number of Super VGAcards.andP;  Or you can do the reverse and translate VGA images to TGA format forfurther coloring.andP;  Reduction algorithms, for example, include &quot;modifiedpopularity&quot; and &quot;median-cut.&quot; The documentation helps you select the bestreduction process.andP;  In addition, there are various dithering, gray scale, andpalette sorting, contrast and brightness options.andM;Phips reads directly only from Targa files, but external conversion utilitiesbundled in the package accept input from .andP;  PCX, .andP;  GIF, TIFF, Mouse SystemsPIC, and ColorRIX .VMG.andP;  It will save to most of these and EPS files, aswell.andP;  Targa files can be saved with compression.andM;Phips uses its own Windows like graphical interface.andP;  Phips's on-screen256-color reductions are the best color images I've seen on my Video 7 VRAM,and I can't believe that the 256 gray-scale images I printed out were reallymade on my HP LaserJet III.andM;List Price: Phips, Version 1.4, $349.andP;  Requirer.: 640K RAM.andP;  TerraVision,2351 College Station Rd., #563, Athens, GA 39605; (404) 769-5641.andO;</TEXT></DOC>